[h1]Auto Login[/h1]
Client-side Fabric mod that automatically logs you into
authentication-based Minecraft servers (e.g. EasyAuth, AuthMe)
using a locally encrypted password.

This mod runs entirely on the client and does [b]not[/b] modify
any server behavior.

[hr]

[h2]Features[/h2]
[list]
[*]Automatically sends [b]/login <password>[/b] after joining a server[/*]
[*]Password is stored [b]locally and encrypted[/b] (AES-GCM with random device key)[/*]
[*]No server-side plugin or mod required[/*]
[*]Client-only, safe for multiplayer servers[/*]
[*]Manual trigger via command for testing or fallback[/*]
[/list]

[hr]

[h2]Commands[/h2]
[h3]Set password (required once)[/h3]
[code]/autologin set <password>[/code]
[list]
[*]Encrypts and saves the password locally[/*]
[*]Enables auto-login automatically[/*]
[/list]

[h3]Trigger auto-login immediately[/h3]
[code]/autologin login[/code]
[list]
[*]Executes login attempt right now[/*]
[*]Useful for testing or manual retry[/*]
[/list]

[h3]Enable / disable[/h3]
[code]/autologin on
/autologin off[/code]
[h3]Clear saved password[/h3]
[code]/autologin clear[/code]
[list]
[*]Deletes stored credentials[/*]
[*]Disables auto-login[/*]
[/list]

[hr]

[h2]How It Works[/h2]
[list]
[*]On first setup, the password is encrypted and saved locally[/*]
[*]When you join a server:
[list]
[*]The mod waits until the client is fully initialized[/*]
[*]Then sends the login command directly to the server[/*]
[/list][/*]
[*]The password is [b]never sent anywhere else[/b] and is not logged[/*]
[/list]

The mod does [b]not[/b] intercept packets, modify UI, or hook into
server authentication logic.

[hr]

[h2]Security Notes[/h2]
[list]
[*]Passwords are stored [b]only on your local machine[/b][/*]
[*]Encryption uses:
[list]
[*][b]Random 256-bit device key[/b] (generated per installation, not derivable from public info)[/*]
[*]AES-GCM (authenticated encryption)[/*]
[/list][/*]
[*]The encryption key is stored in a separate file from the config[/*]
[*]No plaintext password is written to disk[/*]
[*]Do [b]not[/b] reuse important real-world passwords[/*]
[/list]

[hr]

[h2]Supported Versions[/h2]
[list]
[*]Minecraft 1.21.11[/*]
[*]Fabric Loader[/*]
[*]Fabric API[/*]
[*]Java 21[/*]
[/list]

